## Early game

Argon Crystals only come from Argon Deposits — two static containers found in
almost every non-Defense Void tileset, each worth 1-2 crystals. **Hepit**
(Capture, levels 10-15) is a quick way to hit both deposits without needing a
levelled squad. Because these are container pickups, Resource Drop Boosters
and the Steel Path resource passive don't apply to them — the only thing that
matters is how many Void missions you can run. Remember that Argon Crystals
decay: at 00:00 GMT every day, whatever's still decaying gets cut in half, so
don't stockpile more than you're about to spend.

## Mid & late game

**Mot** on the Void (Survival, Steel Path) lets a squad bank as many crystals
as they can before the next decay tick, since an endless Survival means
repeated deposit spawns without resetting the mission. Enemy drops in the same
mission (including anything picked up via Resourceful Retriever or a booster)
still benefit from Steel Path's passive even though the Argon Deposits
themselves don't. Corrupted Vor on his Assassination node is also worth
remembering — he's guaranteed to drop either an Orokin Cell or an Argon
Crystal.

